-- Vale Advances 0.7 Percent in Sao Paulo, Reversing Earlier Slide
-- B y   J u a n   P a b l o   S p i n e t t o
-- 2012-02-16T21:24:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/vale-advances-0-7-percent-in-sao-paulo-reversing-earlier-slide.html
Vale SA (VALE3) , the world’s second-largest
mining company, gained in  Sao Paulo  trading today, reversing
earlier losses.  Vale closed 0.7 percent up at 42.36 reais in Sao Paulo,
extending this year’s gain to 12 percent. The stock dropped as
much as 1.7 percent earlier today after fourth-quarter earnings
missed analysts’ estimates because of declining metal prices.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Juan Pablo Spinetto in Rio de Janeiro at 
 jspinetto@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
